The Health Ministry says almost 854 000 people in the country have received the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine since Phase 2 of the roll out for people over 60 years of age started three weeks ago. Around 483 000 healthcare workers received their vaccinations under the Sisonke Study bringing the total of people vaccinated in South Africa to more than 1,3 million. There are currently 61 557 active cases in the country after another 5 074 were recorded in the last reporting cycle. More than 22 000 of the active cases are in Gauteng. Latest SA stats: SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 341 0123 198 695 66 286 83 763 11 672 2 472 1 459 DEATHS 4 452 11 411 10 534 1 162 86163 474 484 78 836 52 832 296 402  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape 104 073 6 JUNE 2021 1 696 564 56 974 11 876 594 1 578 033 5 073 45 Total Vaccination  1 336 547 11 863 1 ﻿949 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));  